<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2,img,p { margin:0; } td{ padding-top:0 !important; } p {margin-bottom: 10px;}</mj-style>
    <!-- <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" /> -->
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3">

    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    
    <!-- Logo Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/logo.png" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" alt="" />
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.5;
            ">Every successful company has a turning point—a risk that paid off, a product that redefined an industry, or a decision that changed everything. However, not every story is one of triumph; some of the most valuable lessons come from the failures and missteps that shaped the business landscape.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    
    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>

    <!-- Bussiness history -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="2px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          padding-top:14px;
          color:#8C3321;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom:2px solid #8C3321;
              font-size: 26px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              padding-bottom:8px;
            ">The Toyota touch: Engineering efficiency</h2> 
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Looms to cars</h2>  
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;">
          Toyota was founded in 1937 by Kiichiro Toyoda, who came from a family of automation experts. <strong>His father, Sakichi Toyoda, founded Toyoda Automatic Loom Works</strong>. When Kiichiro traveled to America for higher studies, he was fascinated by the thriving automobile industry. When he returned, he convinced his family to invest in automotive development. This was the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-15-02-2025-1-beginning-of-toyota-motors?source=website" target="_blank"> beginning of Toyota Motors</a>.
          </p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/first-toyota-dealership-us-toyota-motor-sales.png" alt="The first Toyota dealership in US, Toyota Motor Sales, USA, Inc., Hollywood, California" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
         <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            The first Toyota dealership in US, Toyota Motor, USA, Inc., Hollywood, California. Credits: Toyota Archives.
          </p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
          From its inception, Kiichiro aimed to expand Toyota beyond Japan. The company’s first major interaction with the US came during the Korean War when the US military ordered over 5,000 vehicles from Toyota. <strong>Toyota formally entered the American market in 1957</strong> with Toyota Motor, USA, Inc., based in Hollywood, California. The company was responsible for selling, promoting, and distributing Toyota vehicles in the United States.
          </p>
        
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>